snippet.textDisplay:
I'm a really close friend of the portuguese rally driver that lost control in 1986 in the Ford RS 200. (same year that me and his son were born, his one of my best friends).
He's probably the best portuguese rally driver ever. Story goes that there was a photographer inside the curve that is not visible in the video, and when he tried to avoid him, he lost control of the car. It was not his fault, and every big car manufactory, from audi to peugeot, sided by him, saying that this disaster was just waiting to happen. At the time, security in Portugal was below none, since people would go to the midle of the road just before the most famous jump in the portugues rally.. After the accident all the WRC Group B drivers were angry since they warned more than once for the lack of security, and refused to drive the next stage because of the public..
The Portugues Driver's name is Joaquim Santos, a 4 time portuguese rally champion and his record of 47 wins in the portugues rally championship still holds today.

Just search "rally group B portugal" in youtube..
